member.remarks:
Ways to pass parameters:
            

No parameters:


rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText);
            

Variable length parameter list:


rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText, 1, 'a', "test", 13.5);
            

Explicit parameter array:


rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText, new object[] {2, "test"});
            

Ways to get back a ref_cursor:  
            

Only output ref_cursor parameters: 


The signature of the procedure:  TestPkg.TestProc1(refCur OUT G3E_DBTYPES.G3E_REF_CURSOR)

  SQL = "TestPkg.TestProc1";

  rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdStoredProc);

Note : Do not give the output parameter
            

Variable length parameter list:


The signature of the procedure:  TestPkg.TestProc2(x IN NUMBER, refCur OUT G3E_DBTYPES.G3E_REF_CURSOR)

  SQL = "TestPkg.TestProc2";

  rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdStoredProc, 1);

Note : Do not specify the output ref_cursor parameter on the parameter list.
            

Explicit parameter array:


The signature of the procedure:  TestPkg.TestProc2(x IN NUMBER, refCur OUT G3E_DBTYPES.G3E_REF_CURSOR)

  SQL = "TestPkg.TestProc2";

  rs = oDataContext.Execute(SQL, out iRecordsAffected, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdStoredProc, new object[] {2});

Note : Do not specify the output ref_cursor parameter on the array.

 Ways to pass parameters:

No parameters:

rs = oDataContext.OpenRecordset(SQL, ADODB.CursorTypeEnum.adOpenStatic, ADODB.LockTypeEnum.adLockReadOnly, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText);

Variable length parameter list:

rs = oDataContext.OpenRecordset(SQL, ADODB.CursorTypeEnum.adOpenStatic, ADODB.LockTypeEnum.adLockReadOnly, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText, 1, 'a', "test", 13.45);

Explicit parameter array:

rs = oDataContext.OpenRecordset(SQL, ADODB.CursorTypeEnum.adOpenStatic, ADODB.LockTypeEnum.adLockReadOnly, (int)ADODB.CommandTypeEnum.adCmdText, new object[] {2, "test"});
